23// Note: If this list changes, also the histogram "V8.LiftoffBailoutReasons"
24// on the chromium side needs to be updated.
25// Deprecating entries is always fine. Repurposing works if you don't care about
26// temporary mix-ups. Increasing the number of reasons {kNumBailoutReasons} is
27// more tricky, and might require introducing a new (updated) histogram.
28enum LiftoffBailoutReason : int8_t {
29 // Nothing actually failed.
30 kSuccess = 0,
31 // Compilation failed, but not because of Liftoff.
32 kDecodeError = 1,
33 // Liftoff is not implemented on that architecture.
34 kUnsupportedArchitecture = 2,
35 // More complex code would be needed because a CPU feature is not present.
36 kMissingCPUFeature = 3,
37 // Liftoff does not implement a complex (and rare) instruction.
38 kComplexOperation = 4,
39 // Unimplemented proposals:
40 kSimd = 5,
41 kRefTypes = 6,
42 kExceptionHandling = 7,
43 kMultiValue = 8,
44 kTailCall = 9,
45 kAtomics = 10,
46 kBulkMemory = 11,
47 kNonTrappingFloatToInt = 12,
48 kGC = 13,
49 kRelaxedSimd = 14,
50 // A little gap, for forward compatibility.
51 // Any other reason (use rarely; introduce new reasons if this spikes).
52 kOtherReason = 20,
53 // Marker:
54 kNumBailoutReasons
55};
56
57struct LiftoffOptions {
58 int func_index = -1;
59 ForDebugging for_debugging = kNotForDebugging;
60 Counters* counters = nullptr;
61 WasmFeatures* detected_features = nullptr;
62 base::Vector<const int> breakpoints = {};
63 std::unique_ptr<DebugSideTable>* debug_sidetable = nullptr;
64 int dead_breakpoint = 0;
65 int32_t* max_steps = nullptr;
66 int32_t* nondeterminism = nullptr;
67
68 // Check that all non-optional fields have been initialized.
69 bool is_initialized() const { return func_index >= 0; }
70
71 // We keep the macro as small as possible by offloading the actual DCHECK and
72 // assignment to another function. This makes debugging easier.
73#define SETTER(field) \
74 LiftoffOptions& set_##field(decltype(field) new_value) { \
75 return Set<decltype(field)>(&LiftoffOptions::field, new_value); \
76 }
77
78 SETTER(func_index)
79 SETTER(for_debugging)
80 SETTER(counters)
81 SETTER(detected_features)
82 SETTER(breakpoints)
83 SETTER(debug_sidetable)
84 SETTER(dead_breakpoint)
85 SETTER(max_steps)
86 SETTER(nondeterminism)
87
88#undef SETTER
89
90 private:
91 template <typename T>
92 LiftoffOptions& Set(T LiftoffOptions::*field_ptr, T new_value) {
93 // The field must still have its default value (set each field only once).
94 DCHECK_EQ(this->*field_ptr, LiftoffOptions{}.*field_ptr);
95 this->*field_ptr = new_value;
96 return *this;
97 }
98};
